  "body": "There is currently no acceptable documentation on geth or in the five different beacon clients. https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/interface/consensus-clients is completely useless besides shipping you to various poorly documented projects without answers to much of anything.\r\n\r\nAll I need to do is start syncing the post-merge chain so I can make the complex web3 queries my data products depend on. Why is this so hard?\r\n\r\nI fully synced my full node on an external drive. I just want to ideally run one client that references past chain data. Nobody has explained if this will be possible, or if it is now. I've been through thousands of videos and articles relating to the merge, and it all seems impossible. How the heck are people supposed to use Ethereum in this condition?\r\n",
