    "body": "If you think e.g https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/ is poorly documented, well, I don't know what to say. \r\n\r\n> I just want to ideally run one client that references past chain data. Nobody has explained if this will be possible, or if it is now. \r\n\r\nNot possible. The documentation basically everywhere, and in the geth process logs, and on our discord, says that you need geth _and_ a beacon node. A.k.a an EL-client and a CL-client. I think it's the single most explained fact about the merge, that node operators now need to run two clients.  \r\n",
