    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/\r\n\r\nYes. That is an example of poor documentation. If this were a side project, ok fine, talk to the developer and help contribute. There's no answer to what I want to do, no attempt to understand the end user, and a complete disregard of decentralization here.\r\n\r\nClosing valid tickets is not going to help. The idea to be language neutral seems good in theory, in practice it is like voting for candidates under socialism. Every single beacon client sucks in a slightly different way. It's not a real choice.\r\n\r\nLodestar is the best beacon client. It works - sort of, and the devs are responsive, unlike here, where everyone knows it all and thinks people are going to continue to run full nodes. Might as well say something nice. I know people are trying, but ignorance is running high now.\r\n\r\nI've been here since 2016, I'm now out. My nodes are not coming back up. Please reference this 'annoying' ticket in the future when things go a lot worse than anyone OG expected. This is a prime example of hubris.\r\n\r\nI wish I wish wrong here. I'm used to being wrong. I still could be wrong, but it sure doesn't seem like it. Best of luck.",
